title: Error: ‘vmsLog2’ was not declared in this scope
body_html:
Hi, I met the following error when building from source. Does anyone have the same issue?

Issue description

aten/src/ATen/cpu/vml.h:68:76: error: ‘vmsLog2’ was not declared in this scope

System Info

  • Build command you used (if compiling from source): python3 setup.py build
  • OS: Ubuntu 16.04
  • PyTorch version: 372d1d6
  • Python version: 3.5.2
  • CUDA/cuDNN version: N/A
  • GPU models and configuration: N/A
  • GCC version (if compiling from source): 5.4
  • CMake version: 3.11.0
